{{Infobox company | name = Refinitiv | image = Refinitiv times square.jpg | image_caption = Refinitiv's offices in Times Square, New York | former_name = Thomson Reuters Financial & Risk | industry = Financial Technology | founded = 2018 | location = [[New York City]], New York, USA | key_people = David Craig (CEO) | revenue = US $6.1 bn<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://annual-report.thomsonreuters.com/financial-performance.html|title=Annual Report 2017|website=Thomson Reuters|access-date=2018-10-19}}</ref> | revenue_year = 2017 | num_employees = 11,000 (2018)<ref name="Refinitiv aims to spend to take on Bloomberg" /> | website = {{URL|https://www.refinitiv.com}} }}
'''Refinitiv''' – formerly the Financial and Risk business of [[Thomson Reuters]] – is a global provider of financial markets data and infrastructure. The new company is jointly owned by [[Blackstone Group]] LP who have a 55% stake in the business and Thomson Reuters who now own 45%<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nasdaq.com/article/thomson-reuters-closes-deal-with-blackstone-20181001-01265|title=Thomson Reuters closes deal with Blackstone|date=2018-10-01|work=NASDAQ.com|access-date=2018-10-18|language=en-us}}</ref> The company has an annual turnover of $6bn with more than 40,000 client companies<ref name="clients">{{Cite web|url=https://www.refinitiv.com/perspectives/financial-crime/meet-refinitiv/|title=Meet Refininitv|access-date=2018-10-01}}</ref> in 190 countries.<ref name="Refinitiv aims to spend to take on Bloomberg">{{Cite web|url=https://www.ft.com/content/ed3bc55e-c490-11e8-8670-c5353379f7c2|title=Refinitiv aims to spend to take on Bloomberg|last=|first=|date=|website=Financial Times|language=en-GB|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-10-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/business/article-refinitiv-ceo-aims-to-kick-start-faster-revenue-growth-for-6-billion/|title=Refinitiv CEO aims to kick-start faster growth for ‘$6-billion startup’ born out of Thomson Reuters-Blackstone deal|access-date=2018-10-19}}</ref>
== History ==
Thomson Reuters Corp sold a 55-percent majority stake in its Financial & Risk (F&R) unit to private equity firm Blackstone Group LP on October 1, 2018, in a deal which valued the total F&R business at about $20 billion. This business was formed into Refinitiv.<ref name=":0" />
==Operations==
Under the deal, Thomson Reuters transferred its complete Financial and Risk product portfolio to Refinitiv, with the exception of Regulatory Intelligence, Risk Compliance Learning and Data Privacy Advisory Services.
Refinitiv's [[FinTech]] data, analytics, trading, and risk assessment tools include [[FXall]], [[Eikon|Eikon Messenger]], Auto Audit and the Elektron Data Platform creating 32,000 risk intelligence records every month from internal and third-party sources. Another, the [https://www.refinitiv.com/en/products/world-check-kyc-screening World-Check Risk Intelligence database], compiles information from international financial watch lists, government records, and media searches to tackle [[Money Laundering]].
Although Thomson Reuters is now a minority shareholder in Refinitiv, it still supplies Reuters news and content to the company's 400,000 plus customers in more than 40,000 businesses around the world, supported by a network of at least 13,000 registered developers.
Refinitiv's Developer Portal includes data feeds, [[Software_development_kit|SDKs]] and [[Application_programming_interface|APIs]], documentation, sample code, learning materials and community Q & A forums. These run alongside "developer days" in regional centres on topics including [[Machine_learning|machine learning]], cloud services and legislation such as [[General_Data_Protection_Regulation|GDPR]].
